title: People Are Strange - Cover
description:
Worked on this one for a bit more time that I expected but it is finally here. The piano part had some issues with the tuning, I was thinking about taking that part out but since I had fun playing that part I decided to leave it there. Hope you like this little tribute to The Doors!

Trabajé un poco más de tiempo del que esperaba con esta pista pero finalmente está aquí. La parte del teclado tiene algunas cuestiones en cuanto a afinación, por un momento pensé retirarlo pero como me divertí creando esa parte decidí dejarlo. Espero les guste este pequeño homenaje a The Doors!

title: 'Cause life is for living
description:
Fríos han sido estos días, mi habitacion ni se diga ...
Estamos a pocos días de terminar por fin un año mas, y de comenzar uno nuevo. He estado practicamente aislado desde que ha empezado esta digamos "cuenta regresiva", pero sin embargo he decidido hacer una sola cosa mas. Es con esta pequeña pieza con la que quisiera concluir mi actividad en este sitio para este año. Sé que el trabajo quizás no es de muy buena calidad o que trato de sonar como un profesional. Lo que si sé es que soy alguien más haciendo lo que todo el mundo hace; hacer lo que a uno le gusta. Por su atención, ¡muchas gracias!

title: entrevista a emilo ahumada desde brasil
description:
desde uspallata-alta montaña, a traves de radio comunitaria la pakita, en el espacio "EL DES PROGRAMA", merlina giri entrevistó a emilio ahumada . ..

Emilio A. Ahumada
Después de nacer en San Martín, Mendoza, a los 6 meses su familia se traslada a localidad de
Tunuyán (Tierra que se mueve) donde sus padres le comparten su amor por la Madre Tierra,
visitando ríos, montañas y participando de actividades comunitarias como procesamiento
artesanal de alimentos para preservarlos en el tiempo.
Aun a corta edad comienza a ser evidente su interés por los procesos naturales, cuando colocó
su oreja en el piso para escuchar que sucedía durante el sismo 6,3 grados Richter, de 1985 con
epicentro en Barrancas Mendoza. También se impregna en su retina el paso del cometa Halley
en 1986.
Su vida familiar le permitió desarrollar dones para desplegarse cómodamente en el campo,
habilidades manuales en la construcción, la metalurgia y la tecnología.
Su atracción por Pachamama favorece el estudio de la Geología en la Universidad de San Luis,
donde realizó estudios de grado y de postgrado, especializándose en tratar de comprender
3
como crecen las montañas y su relación con la actividad símica, con el gran sueño de disminuir
o mitigar las catástrofes que este fenómeno genera. Con la necesidad de incorporar y
desarrollar conocimientos que permitan habitar nuestro entorno de una manera más armónica
y consciente, trabaja desde la Geobiología y Geología Médica, intentando comprender como
los factores geofísicos y geoquímicos afectan la salud, así como también procesos
geopatógenos favorecidos por el hombre, sumando más 10 años de experiencia en el medio.
También transita caminos ancestrales profundizando en conocimientos de medicinas sagradas
y técnicas de autoconocimiento. Brindando asistencia, acompañamiento y contención en
ceremonias sagradas por más de 5 años en diferentes lugares de Brasil y Argentina.
Fue colaborador del Instituto de Permacultura Na Lu´um Argentina, integrando en forma
vivencial, práctica e intuitiva, todos los aspectos que han dejado impronta en su vida
Actualmente vive y se desempeña en la comunidad Naçao Tutumbaie (Centro de Medicinas
Sagradas Ancestrales) Santa María Rio Grande do Sul, Brasil; conjuntamente con su compañera
Sofía y su bebe Beijamim, desarrollando integración de Caminos Espirituales,
Autoconocimiento, Permacultura, además de cultivar la conciencia a través de la Alimentación
Holística, con el objetivo de favorecer el despertar de la conciencia y la re-conexión con la
Madre Tierra, el Tata Inti y el Todo!

title: 02 Don't You Ever Get Tired
description: I was bass player/vocalist with Grammy award winning DJ King Edward Smith IV  who was a go to session guitarist as well as a recording studio owner and renounced  producer. We had just finished a show backing Tom T Hall,Billy Joe Burnette,and The Statler Brothers and had returned to Roanoke and gone straight to the studio to lay down some tracks for Mr Hall.(most musicians seem to do there best work late at night especially recording)K E played him my track of legendary song writer Hank Cochran's" Don't You Ever Get Tired "(of Hurting Me)that we had done for an upcoming album. About 3 days after the session with Mr Hall I was visited by the chief A&R man with Mercury and a rep from Buddy Lee Talent in Nashville. With K E as my agent I was signed to record for the Treetop Label a subsideary of Mercury. This cut was my first release and reached #43 nationally and even hit #3 on the Texas charts. Needless to say I wish I had been wiser in making some of the decisions I made back then. But this opened a lot of doors and I am blessed to have had this opportunity. Good memories for Susie and I

title: Port Damali (A Widow's Mourning - Cover By Merle)
description:
Original shanty by Morgan Slade on YouTube. You can find the original here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ddz1Fw5Oz6E
Lyrics (partly based on the original) and voice by Merle.

LYRICS:
Every sailor leaves hopeful and cocky
Every lover sleeps cold and afraid
That your spyglass will roam or you'll never come home
As you sail away from Port Damali

And you say: "Yo, this place here ain't my home
I was sent here to roam, unafraid, sailing storms, not alone
Hand over the key to your heart cause we won't grow apart
A new start Port Damali"

They say sailors trade comfort for glory
They say lovers trade hope for betrayal
Cause my faith has grown thin as his love whithers
Trimming the sails far away Port Damali

And I think: 'He wasn't here for your soul 
was just after the gold in your hold and then leaves you alone
Charms his way to your heart, we make love, then depart"
Empty promises in Port Damali

Every danger's your call for adventure
Every treasure's your siren in need
But the music shall fade
once you see what's at stake
As I wait for you in Port Damali

Did you find what you lost? Was it just
an escape from the grief? Did you leave
to find peace overseas?
Was it peace that I couldn't provide?
Just hold tight, just come home
to me in Port Damali

Will my sailor's last breath hold the ocean
Will my tears ever water his grave
Oh, my heart can't afford a disaster aboard
How my heart feels sore Port Damali

And I think: 'You of all people should know
I'll stay always alone cause my heart belongs only to you
I won't wait no more, I'll simply dream 'til I see the sun set
No regrets Port Damali

As years of waiting go by I still see you
In the sea and the shanties and ships
I grow older in knowing you'll never come home
But I'm proud to have known Port Damali

title: Chocolate Beer (2018 12 31 )
description:
Steven and Merle Industries
Proudly bring you Chocolate Beer Chocolate Beer 
Don't give it to dogs cause they'll get diarrhoea 

Chocolate Beer, Chocolate Beer - it's the perfect treat for this time of year
A glass and a half of full-strength lager in every piece of Chocolate Beer
How do Steven and Merle manage to fit a glass and a half of full-strength lager in every piece of Chocolate Beer?

Keep it away from dogs and cats
They'll get sick if they get stuck into that
Chocolate Beer, Chocolate Beer, it's the perfect thing for this time of year
Chocolate Beer
Don't leave it in ya car on a hot day
Cause when you come back your chocolate'll be running away
Down the street cause there's a lot of beer in Chocolate Beer

title: Loch Ness Monster (2019 04 01 )
description:
Loch Ness Monster

Steven and Merle went camping 
Camping at Loch Ness
They'd been in Scotland a while
And wanted to go camping
Steven went to Merle "I'm going fishing in the morning."
Merle rolled over and went back to be because he was tired
Steven had his box and his favourite rod
He cast it in Loch Ness and got a few nibbles.
He was about to pack it up
But then he got a bite, he thought "That's a really big fish"
And then he adjusted the drag

But he'd caught the Loch Ness Monster
The sonsie Loch Ness Monster
Steven was water skiing
Behind the Loch Ness Monster

Steven was on the loch
And Roger the dog was barking
Barking at his master
Who's going behind the monster

Water skiing on the loch 
You wouldn't believe your eyes
If you saw Steven skiing behind the Loch Ness Monster

Nessie took him out to the middle of the loch 
He threw his rod right down
And he had to swim back to shore

He went back to Merle
He was dripping wet
Merle said "What happened? You fell into the loch?"
Steven said "You wouldn't believe me if I told you anyway
But I caught the Loch Ness Monster
The sonsie LNM
That cheeky LNM
He took away my rod

Merle said "You're lying, you're telling me a fib. I wouldn't believe ya"
But when he turned around, it was The Loch Ness Monster
He had Steven's rod
and he gave it back to Steven
The great big Loch Ness Monster he had Steven's rod
He gave it back to Steven and said "Sorry about your rod, but I broke it clean in half, I broke your rod in half"
Steven said "I don't mind cause I've got another one. Thank you LNM, come and have some porridge. We're going to have some breakfast and a bowl of porridge

You can have a whisky we're drinking at the loch cause we're camping here all week
We got some things we'd like to see"
And the LNM said "Jump on my back and I'll take you across the loch to the place in the middle of the loch and I'll show you round the loch if you stay on my back I'll take you round the loch 
I'll swim you to the middle and then you can get off in the middle of the loch"
Roger the dog was barking he couldn't believe his eyes cause he'd never seen a monster. Time for the solo.

title: My Cousin Ben (2019 03 11)
description:
Cut me some slack
I'm the best there ever was
You all loved me back then
I'm your brother Ben
The best mid fielder there ever was
Gettin' the ball down the other end of the oval
There's nobody better than me

My brother Ben, he's at it again
Will we win by six goals, or will it be ten?

We're winning again, thanks to Ben
Michael Gardiner, and Daniel Kerr and all those guys you slag off now
Back then you loved them like everyone, so cut them some slack

title: Dog In The Rain (2019 03 25)
description:
I'm a dog in the rain
Left me outside again

I went outside to have a wee
And they closed the door behind me 
I think it's cause they trust me in the back yard while they're at work all day

Well I'm just glad that I buried a pair of slippers under a tree
That'll keep me company
That'll keep me busy
Till they get home and it's time for dinner

I'm a dog in the rain
They left me outside again
I got nothin' to do so I guess I'll just dig another hole right here for you

I bet you'll be so proud of me when you get home from work
You can plant a tree in it
You can bury your food in it
I'll let you put your food in the hole

I know you're got a refrigerator
But you should try burying your food in a hole for later
It works for dogs, why do humans like their food to be fresh and cold?

Just dig a hole and put it in it 

Okay all the poodles in the house

Now all the German Shepherds in the house

Now all the wolfhounds

We're all dogs in the rain
In the neighbourhood
They left us outside, whaddya expect us to do? Bark, so we can hear the news
I can't wait for you to get home from work so I can tell bout my day
And show you the hole I dug
There's a poodle down the street
She's been yapping all day

I'm a dog in the rain 
Ain't got any gumboots
Got soggy paws again

Why don't you get me one of those doggy raincoats, or build me a kennel or something at least? 

Why do dogs smell like they do when they've been out in the rain?

title: Calendar Dog (2019 04 08)
description:
He's got big pointy ears
All the better to hear you with
Waiting for a command 
Waiting for someone to throw him a frisbee
But my German Shepherd he wasn't very good at retrieving 
He'd rather that I'd chase him through the garden
He'd get the frisbee and I'd have to chase him around

title: Sorry Salvador (2019 04 08)
description:
2019_04_08

I gotta go soon, Steven, I better start packing up soon
I'll see you next week; same place, about the same time if I wake up and get ready

I'm so lazy, especially in the morning 
And the dog is looking at me.
He's saying take me for a walk
I have to apologise to the dog and say "I don't have time for a walk this morning, I'll take you for one when I get home"
He just puts down his ears
He looks at me with a sad face
I've never seen such a sad face in my life, as Salvador the dog when I tell him we don't have time for a walk  
I'm sorry Salvador you'll have to wait till I get home
We can walk round the block and you can have a crap on the neighbours' lawn
Sorry Salvador

Dikit ja. nanti yang fullnya.
Lagu ini sangat sangat mewakili keadaan rasa saat ini. Mewakili keadaan hati saat ini. Kelimpungan, Gila. aku gila menggilainya mencintainya. Tidak ada yang mampu menggantikannya, atau hanya saja belum. Benar saja, rasa ini di tanam setahun yang lalu oleh Tuhan, yang dulu aku sudah meninggalkannya tanpa mencabut akarnya. Saat ini rasa ini tumbuh besar di dalam dada hendakkeluar dan memberontak, menuntut temu kasihnya yang di surakarta. Rindu yang menjadi buah, ranum hendak jatuh ke pelukannya. title: EMA helistab. Helina Savi. Menstruatsiooniveri on ilus.
description:
Seekord helistas ajakirja EMA peatoimetaja Merle Liivak Helina Savile, kes on ema ja ettevõtja, veebipoe viljakusmonitor.ee looja. Tänu Helinale on Eesti naistel võimalik tutvuda ja soetada selliseid intrigeerivalt kõlavaid vahendeid nagu vaagnapõhjalihaste trenažöör, viljakusmonitor, lekkekindel pesu jne. Neist kahest viimasest tuleb saates juttu lähemalt, muu seas saame teada ka seda, miks menstruatsiooniveri on ilus. 

Saade on valminud koostöös.

“EMA helistab” on koroonakarantiinis sündinud taskuhääling, mida juhib ajakirja EMA peatoimetaja Merle Liivak, noppimaks toetavaid mõtteid ja inspiratsiooni. Eks ikka selleks, et vibratsioonid püsiksid epideemiale vaatamata kõrgel!

title: Little Robot Heart
description:
This is a very important song to me; it's one of my favourite songs.
It has this very unique feel to it - the drums and the koto set up this intense atmosphere to this song,
and the guitars work with that atmosphere.
The drums play this robot heart beating motif almost over the entire length of the song.
It sounds nothing like a human heart - yet it is a four-stroke-heart(which is somewhat close to a human heart).
This is really an integral part of it - this song has a really strong connection to its name, unlike actually many of my other songs.

La Gigue
description:
Vieillerie qui prenait la poussière, extrait d'une série radio sur le jazz, recyclé au sein d'un fourre-tout audio événementiel pour l'asso Breizh SteamPunk Society.
À l'époque, mon patron voulait une série d'émissions sur le jazz, mais comme je m'y connaissais à peu près autant qu'en art pariétal, j'ai pris le parti d'écrire en 20 minutes des capsules incultes et de mauvaise foi en prenant un titre complètement par hasard.
Pour cacher le fait que ça serait une ânerie radiophonique de plus, j'ai embarqué ma collègue de l'époque, Gwen, qui n'a pas sa pareille pour lire avec le plus grand sérieux mes chroniques aux phrases trop longues qui investissaient à l'époque sur les virgules. Je n'en utilisais pas, je les gardais pour plus tard.
Le titre en question est l'interprétation de Dansons la gigue par Patricia Barber.

description: Hey ondernemer in deze aflevering breng ik je helemaal op de hoogte van de ontwikkelingen van de afgelopen tijd.

title: Aflevering 3 - Samenwerken
description: Krijg motivatie, inspiratie tools en life hacks zodat je met nog meer vrijheid en zelfvertrouwen kunt gaan ondernemen en leven. Merle neemt je mee op ondernemers avontuur zodat je slimmer gaat ondernemen, de snelle routes, loopholes en de shortcuts gaat ontdekken. Stel je voor dat alles kan?! Wat zou er dan mogelijk voor je zijn? Merle laat je zien dat het leven een groot experiment is en dat ALLES mogelijk is. Want als jij groeit als mens en ondernemer, kan je nog meer mensen helpen met je prachtige ideeën, zodat je bedrijf gaat groeien, je meer impact maakt op de wereld en een verschil maakt in het leven van anderen. Lets go!

description:
I am not a medical expert but this podcast is based on my experience with my father who lost his life because of depression. Giving an advice to a depressed has risks and these are the lessons that I learned because of my father's passing from depression. 

I apologize for the pop on some parts of this audio track. I recorded this via my cellular phone.

description:

I dedicate this podcast to all the people who have lost a loved one because of depression. My father died because of depression on March 21, 2013. Sending all my love to everyone who's suffering from depression.

Audio by Jurrivh via https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zMvCfm_AjYo

title: Moi, Changelin
description:
Paroles :

Il se pourrait que je sois un changelin car aucun de mes ancêtres n’a jamais eu cet œil brun crevant de vert au soleil. Je n’ai nulle part trouvé d’intelligence ou d’idiotie comparable à la mienne et, après tant d’années, je peine encore à me retourner lorsqu’on m’appelle. Mes grains de beauté changent de place, surtout la nuit, lorsque l’océan se déchaîne. Il m’arrive aussi de danser à propos de sculpture ou de me tenir en déséquilibre au sommet de grimoires empilés. Mon analphabétisme n’est pas un problème.

Inutile de miauler, je comprends le silence des chats.

Il est possible que je sois un changelin car je suis capable de compter sur mes doigts jusqu’à l’infini. Bien des choses m’échappent, comme ce verre de cristal si soudain. Mais il ne tombe pas, il s’élève brusquement vers le sol. Mes pieds sont en sang, il ne s’est pas brisé. Un jour, on m’a ordonné de faire comme tout le monde. En observant mes semblables, je me suis donc mis à tapisser mes poches de papier, mais je suis resté nu. J’ignore l’art du mimétisme.

Pour me parler de philosophie, il faut aboyer très fort.

C’est certain, je suis un changelin car je m’étonne toujours de voir les coquilles d’œuf jetées au feu. De plus, j’ai peur du fer et de tous les métaux qui m’évoquent la guerre. Instinctivement, les hommes m’évitent. Seules les bêtes supportent ma présence car je porte leur odeur. N’ayant pas réussi à rassembler les rameaux d’or pour faire mon nid, je me suis enfui. Oui, fini les rites secrets au sommet des collines. Je suis passé en sens inverse à travers les pierres creuses. Mais maintenant, suis-je chez moi ?

Tu peux siffler, je connais la langue des oiseaux.

title: Pauvre Robin
description:
Paroles :

Qui a tué Robin ?
Moi, dit la grièche,
En tirant ma flèche
J’ai tué Robin.
Qui l’a vu mourir ?
Moi, dit le héron,
De mes grands yeux ronds
Je l’ai vu mourir.
Qui a pris son sang ?
Moi, dit le bruant,
Dans un récipient
J’ai pris de son sang.

Pauvre Robin

Qui tissera son suaire ?
Moi, dit le tarier,
Laissez-moi filer,
Je tisserai son suaire.
Qui creusera sa tombe ?
Moi, dit la sarcelle,
En m’aidant d’une pelle
Je creuserai sa tombe.
Qui, sera le prêtre ?
Moi dit le vautour,
S’il fait encore jour
Je serai le prêtre.

Pauvre Robin

Qui tiendra l’office ?
Moi, dit l’alouette,
Si le temps s’y prête
Je tiendrai l’office.
Qui sera pleureuse ?
Moi, dit la colombe,
Comme mes larmes tombent
Je serai pleureuse.
Qui chantera le psaume ?
Moi, dit le pinçon,
Depuis les buissons
Je chanterai le psaume.

Pauvre Robin

Qui portera la boîte ?
Moi, dirent le canard,
L’oie et le busard,
Nous porterons la boîte.
Qui fera l’éloge ?
Moi, dit la corneille,
S’il y a du soleil
Je ferai l’éloge.
Qui sonnera le glas ?
Moi, dit l’épervier,
Du haut du clocher
Je sonnerai le glas.

Pauvre Robin

Pour le rouge gorge robin
Les oiseaux en grand chagrin
Seront tous là demain.

title: Mon seul désir
description:
La hampe élancée,
Rugueuse
Au toucher
Ressemble à la corne
Soyeuse
Qui front orne.

Les fruits sont sucrés
Pareils
Aux dragées
Offertes à l’oiseau,
Soleil
Au fourneau.

Les fleurs sont tressées,
Couronnes
Parfumées
Dont l’odeur persiste,
Personne
N’y résiste.

L’orgue est de sortie,
La buse
Pousse un cri,
Se joint au concert
Qui fuse
Dans les airs.

Reflets chatoyants,
Miroir
Déformant
Où s’échangent deux
Regards
Amoureux.
tag_list: poésie licorne neofolk neo-folk "wyrd folk" "indie folk"

title: Eclat Élémentaire
description:
Paroles :

J’ai longtemps cherché
Cette mélodie mystérieuse,
Entêtante mais insaisissable
Que je percevais au fond de moi
Durant l’enfance.

La nuit, au crépuscule ou à l’aurore,
Loin, à l’ombre des montagnes
Ou dans le lit blanc du fleuve,
Sur l’immense tapis des plaines
Ou sous les sombres pins,
En ces lieux où seuls la rêverie et l’errance
Peuvent mener
Elle est là !

C’est le souffle qui m’inspire,
La sève qui me nourrit,
Le battement sourd de mon cœur-tambour.
Un sentiment ancien et nouveau à la fois
Qui naît, croît et meurt au grès des saisons.

Combien de vies antérieures depuis notre dernière naissance ?

Qu’il est dur de poser des mots
Sur cette musique sans paroles
Et de faire jaillir
L’éclat élémentaire
Qu’un poème traduit
Et trahit
Comme le parfum profond
Et pourtant si simple
De la rose.
